"'''Empire Blues: The Devaronian's Tale'''" is a short story written by [[Daniel Keys Moran]] for ''[[Tales from the Mos Eisley Cantina]]'', which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[August]] [[1995]]. It takes place in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]].

==Plot summary==
[[Kardue'sai'Malloc/Legends|Kardue'sai'Malloc]] is a former [[Imperial Army/Legends|Imperial army]] [[Officer/Legends|officer]] who committed atrocities on his home world of [[Devaron/Legends|Devaron]]. Now he lives on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] as a fugitive under the alias of '''Labria'''. He recall his [[Blood/Legends|bloody]] past while also reflecting upon his true passion: [[Music/Legends|music]]. When Labria hears that [[Figrin D'an/Legends|Figrin D'an]] and the [[Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes|Modal Nodes]] are playing at [[Lady/Legends|Lady]] [[Valarian/Legends|Valarian's]] [[Marriage/Legends|wedding]], he arranges an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] crackdown at the nuptials and gives the band a refuge by setting them up at his favorite watering hole, the [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]].

